FT  01 FEB 92 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pepper market has picked up, reports Man-producten. Black pepper firmer on
fewer offers from Brazil at higher prices and limited material offered by
other origins. Spot traded at USDollars 1,275 to Dollars 1,300 a tonne,
Jan/Feb shipment at Dollars 1,175 cif. White pepper, on the contrary, tended
weaker on failing demand, ample supplies in origin and increased selling
pressure. Spot about Dollars 1,350 and Jan/Feb shipment at Dollars 1,275
cif.
