<TEXT>
SCOTT PAPER, the world's largest manufacturer of toilet tissue, has revealed
a fourth-quarter net loss of Dollars 157.7m, after taking a large charge for
restructuring and a cut of 3,800 jobs, around 10 per cent of its workforce.
The company warned this month it would be taking a Dollars 183m after-tax
special charge, about half of it due to job cuts. The figure also includes a
gain from the sale of its Japanese joint venture.
