with a loss of Dollars 51.5m, or 70 cents, a year earlier. Excluding special
items, earnings per share dropped from 66 cents to 35 cents. Sales totalled
Dollars 1.32bn, against Dollars 1.43bn.
For the full year, it suffered a net loss of Dollars 69.9m after special
items, or 95 cents, against profits of Dollars 148m, or Dollars 2.01. The
1991 figures do not include businesses to be divested.
