<TEXT>
ABOUT 22,000 mortgage customers of National Home Loans, the troubled lending
group, have been told by Sun Alliance that their payment protection
insurance scheme is to be halted from the end of next month, David Barchard
and Richard Lapper write.
Sun Alliance took over the scheme from Security Pacific, the US banking
group, in August. The decision to end it was taken because the account had
proved 'unprofitable'. Sun Alliance is not withdrawing from payment
protection business in general.
NHL said it expects to sign a new payment protection insurance scheme with
an insurer next week. The scheme will be slightly more expensive for NHL
customers.
About 750 NHL mortgagees are claiming on their payment protection policies
from Sun Alliance. Their claims will not be affected.
