   JOHANNESBURG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
South Africa's main industries and political, community and education
organisations launched a multi-million dollar drive yesterday to improve the
quality of the country's crisis-ridden black education, Reuter reports from
Johannesburg.
Signatories of the R500m (Pounds 106m) trust fund said it was founded
